台灣大學寫作教學中心-英文寫作基礎
















英文寫作基礎



			「英文寫作基礎」旨在幫助學生熟悉學術寫作基本架構。內容著重於文章的結構組織，並使用本中心研究團隊，針對台灣研究生所設計的學術文法與學術字彙教材，培養學生文法語用功能應用與使用專業學術用字及其搭配詞的能力，希望藉由文本分析及寫作練習，為學生奠下扎實的學術寫作基礎。
			
英文寫作基礎課程包含：

段落與文章基本架構
五大學術文體
學術寫作文法
學術單字
閱讀技巧
自我編修技巧
同儕互評技巧
批判思考


				※ 本課程著重教授寫作相關技巧，研究內容與方法不在教學範圍內。若需編修校訂服務，請參考本中心諮詢編修網頁。
			



Fundamentals of English Writing


Course Description

Fundamentals of English Writing intends to equip graduate students with fundamental skills of writing English for academic purposes. This course includes two hours of lecture on expository writing plus one hour on grammatical functions. Topics to be covered include common rhetorical patterns for English paragraph/essay development, essential grammar for academic writing, and collocational learning of vocabulary. In-class writing exercises and take-home individual and group assignments are given to enhance students’ familiarity with the skills taught in this course.
			
Course Objectives
By the end of the course, students will

understand common rhetoric modes in English writing.
apply their knowledge of English grammar for academic writing purposes.
demonstrate familiarities with vocabulary frequently used in academic discourse.
identify and edit their own sentence problems.

Course Content


Preliminaries to Writing

Reading
Vocabulary building
Sentence structure
Functional approach to grammar
Unity and Coherence
Organization



Patterns of Paragraph/Essay Writing

Process
Cause and Effect
Comparison and Contrast
Classification
Argumentation



Course Requirements:

Students are required to attend all classes. No more than three excused absences are permitted.
Active participation in class discussions is required.
Quizzes and a comprehensive final exam are included in this course. No make-up quizzes/exam will be allowed.
Writing assignments are carefully scheduled as stages toward the fulfillment of the course’s objectives. Late assignments will not be accepted.

Core Competencies (CCs)

Professional knowledge and skills
Independent judgment and critical thinking
Teamwork
Interpersonal Communication skills

